<h1>Changelog</h1>
<br/>



<h2>3.0.22 - 2010-01-28</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			WebPOPV: Fixed piping notes window issues with IE6 & 7. Increased default PCD form height.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.20 - 2010-01-25</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			WebPOPV: Piping Classes combo box now loads when adding the first item to a BOM.
		</li>
		<li>
			General: Fixed the "You are being redirected" message for some users.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.18 - 2010-01-15</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			WebPOPV: Admins can now select and delete multiple Piping Class Detail records. Use wisely!
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.17 - 2010-01-11</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Login - Created a new login screen to make it easier to login to POPV.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.16 - 2009-12-22</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			WebPOPV - Valves PDF: Fixed a small bug in the Line Class Valve Sheet PDF where there were duplicate components because of multiple valves for one class.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.15 - 2009-12-18</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			WebPOPV - Valves PDF: Updated the Line Class Valve Sheet PDF to include Manufacturers and Figure Numbers.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.14 - 2009-12-11</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			WebPOPV - Piping Components: Now prevents admins from deleting components that
			are tied to Class Details. Also prevents deletion if the component has subcomponents.
		</li>
		<li>
			WebPOPV - Valves: Updated the Valve Sheet PDFs to include Manufacturers and Figure Numbers.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.13 - 2009-12-08</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Piping Classes: Updated the clone class feature for piping classes so it doesn't record
			the cloning of all details in the Revision History.
		</li>
		<li>
			Added Manufactures and Figure No to the valves comparison view.
		</li>
		<li>
			Anyone can now view the archived status checkbox for Valves.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.12 - 2009-12-08</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			WebPOPV: Refreshes the Valves drop down when a valve is added or modified.
		</li>
		<li>
			Orders: Set default Status to 'Ordered' when creating a new Order.
		</li>
		<li>
			PipingClassDetails: Fixed an issue where if a valve was set to 0, it would fail.
		</li>
		<li>
			PipingComponent: Now requires a description.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.11 - 2009-12-04</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			WebPOPV: Fixed the Bill of Materials Excel download.
		</li>
		<li>
			Material Requests: Fixed a routing error when a search result doesn't find anything.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>


<h2>3.0.10 - 2009-12-03</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			WebPOPV: Now, when trying to add a new figure_no for a manufacturer that doesn't exist to a valve, the manufacturer drop-down now reloads after having created the Manufacturer. Previously it would not show the new one in the drop-down.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>


<h2>3.0.9 - 2009-12-03</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Added the deployment site name to the header, underneath "Material Tracker" so people can distinguish between
			the different BP web site deployments (Carson, Cherrypoint, etc).
		</li>
		<li>
			WebPOPV: Updated the Piping Class All Valves PDF so it now includes Valve Type, Rating, and Body.
		</li>
		<li>
			WebPOPV: Fixed a bug with the BOM CSV export.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.8 - 2009-12-02</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Searching: Added wildcard searching for Purchase Orders and Material Requests.
		</li>
		<li>
			Material Requests: Updated the planners drop-down box so it shows only planners.
		</li>
		<li>
			Material Requests: "Reference Type" field now a textfield with autocomplete functionality.
		</li>
		<li>
			Material Requests: Email now correctly fills in the reference number and it's type.
		</li>
		<li>
			Bill of Materials: CSV now accounts for reference numbers and their types.
		</li>
		<li>
			Reference Number Types: Admins can now define which Type will be the default for 
			new Material Requests.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.7 - 2009-12-01</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Fixed the Purchase Order Reports after the server migration.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.6 - 2009-11-30</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			WebPOPV: Fixed the "All Piping Classes" PDF generation.
		</li>
		<li>
			Fixed a bug with printing Orders.
		</li>
		<li>
			Fixed an issue with editing an Order.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.5 - 2009-11-25</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Updated searching to use a new back-end database indexing program.
		</li>
		<li>
			Updated the groups filtering and assignment so it is more robust and less invasive when searching.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.4 - 2009-11-24</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			WebPOPV: Removed viewing restrictions of Valve Preferred Manufacturers, so now
			everyone can see them. Only Admins can edit though still.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.3 - 2009-11-11</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			WebPOPV: Imported the Piping Subcomponent list.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.2 - 2009-11-09</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			WebPOPV: Only the "Piping Classes" tab shows up upon startup. Removed
			"Revision History" to avoid confusion. This can still be accessed by
			clicking on the "Revision History" link on the left.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<br/>

<h2>3.0.1 - 2009-11-06</h2>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Added Maintenance notifications to alert users 24 hours before
			we deploy a new version (bug fixes exempt - we deploy as soon as 
			they are fixed).
		</li>
		<li>
			"Material Tracker" title link now routes to the home page.
		</li>
		<li>
			"Telaeris" logo now routes to creating a new ticket.
		</li>
		<li>
			Fixed the look of this Changelog!
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
